6.  Running AcqirisDemo & Getting Started

The AcqirisDemo program can simply be run by entering:

    AcqirisDemo

When starting this program, the system can complain about a missing dependency
on libqt-mt.so.3. Indeed, AcqirisDemo requires the Qt3 gui library to be
present on your system to be able to run. Install it using the system package
manager of your distribution: apt-get, yum, or YaST.


The Linux GetStarted sample programs can be created without the need of an
additional development application. Enter the following commands:

    cp -r /usr/src/agilent/acqiris/examples examples
                      Copy the example directory and all of its contents
    cd examples/Linux Change to this new directory containing the makefile
    make              Compile and link the example programs

Note that the include and library paths are defined in the Makefile.

The GetStarted8bitSingleSegment.cpp file contains a simple user program which:
    has globally allocated buffers to achieve optimal readout performance
    finds the Acqiris digitizers on the target machine
    initializes the first (or only) one
    configures some acquisition parameters (and rereads them for checking)
    loops (100 times) over a cycle that
    -   starts the acquisition
    -   waits for it to terminate
    -   reads the waveform 




