Agilent Acqiris Software 4.0a (November 30, 2009)
=============================

This version of Agilent Acqiris Software works with Linux distributions
based on kernels 2.6, either 32 bits or 64 bits. Note that the 64 bits
version supports 32 bits compatibility mode.

Device Driver: Uses version 4.17.2.181
    loadable kernel module version 2.0.0 (for Linux 2.6 kernels)
    loadable kernel module version 1.4.2  (for Linux 2.4 kernels)
AcqirisDemo: Uses version 3.12.1.243

Linux specific changes
- Changed name of kernel module to acqiris (instead of acqrsPCI).
- Added full native 64 bits support for 2.6 kernels.
- Added full support for multi-process operations.
  (see functions Acqrs_suspendControl and Acqrs_resumeControl)
- Added changes for compliance with kernel 2.6.30.
- Added init.d script for easy startup configuration.

Other Changes
- Added support for U1084A001 Averager and PeakTDC options
- Added support for DP1400/U1071Ax RevB
- Extended '_calLoad/Save' support to all digitizer families except
DC440/DP310 families
- Fixed DP1400, U1071Ax, bad samples at end of acquisition when using
forceTrig(0)
- Fixed DP1400, U1071Ax, 16 samples shift in combine x2 at/below 250MS/s
- Fixed configuration of Control I/O for TC84x
- Fixed 'calLoad/Save' not restoring AC trigger values forDC282/DC152/DP1400
families
- Fixed bad 1st acquisition after switching between internal and external
reference for TCxxx modules
- Fixed error 'wrong or not loaded FPGA' after 'resumeControl' or
'powerSystem' for DC440, AP2xx, SCxxx and ACxxx families
- Fixed 'configAvgConfig', 'getInstrumentInfo' and 'calRequired' raising
'Access Violation' when called with invalid parameters

FPGA .bit files:
